# Resource Usage Report

Before the main body of **every user-facing reply**, prepend a **Resources used** section.

## Before composing the reply

1. **Read** `logs/resource-ledger/active.json` when the workspace has a project root (skip in Ask/read-only mode if the read is blocked).
2. If the file is missing, stale, or unreadable, fall back to self-reported data only (see below).

## Format

Use this structure (omit empty rows; do not invent entries):

```markdown
## Resources used

| Kind | Used | Source |
|------|------|--------|
| Rules | security.mdc, token-efficiency.mdc | ledger or context |
| Skills | audit-codebase-cleanup (matched), review-pull-request (read) | ledger |
| Agents | DOCS ‚Äî "add test comments", BACKEND_PYTHON ‚Äî "review pytest style" | ledger or Task tool |
| MCP | user-github ‚Äî list_releases | ledger or CallMcpTool |
| Hooks (executed) | beforeSubmitPrompt:log-resource-usage.ps1, stop:log-resource-usage.ps1 | ledger only |

---
```

Then continue with the normal answer after the `---` divider.

## Accuracy rules

- **Rules**: Prefer `rules` from the ledger. Otherwise list **every** always-applied and file-scoped rule visible in the current context. Do not list rules that were only "available" in the catalog but not applied.
- **Skills**: Build the row from ledger fields (dedupe by skill name; omit the row only when all sources are empty):
  - `skills_matched` ‚Äî keyword routing from prompt text (`routing.py` via hook; tag `(matched)`)
  - `skills_payload` ‚Äî Cursor-supplied matched skills on submit (tag `(payload)` when not already matched/read)
  - `skills_read` ‚Äî `SKILL.md` read via Read tool this turn (tag `(read)`; also self-report with source `Read on SKILL.md` when ledger is stale)
  - Format: comma-separated `` `name` (matched) ``, `` `name` (read) ``, or `` `name` (matched, read) `` when both apply.
  - When the user asks for code review, cleanup, duplication, dead code, security review, or architecture review, cross-check that expected skills appear in `skills_matched` or `skills_read`; if matched but not read, **read** the relevant `SKILL.md` before executing (see `ai-guardrails.mdc`).
- **Agents / subagents**: Prefer `subagents` from the ledger. List **every** spawned subagent as `INVOKE ‚Äî "task summary"` (use `type` and `task` from the ledger). Also cross-check `agents_requested`: each invoke name there must have a matching spawned subagent before you finish the turn (see `ai-guardrails.mdc`). Self-report only subagents you spawned via the Task tool this turn when the ledger is unavailable.
- **MCP**: Prefer `mcp` from the ledger. List each entry as `server ‚Äî tool` using the ledger object's `server` and `tool` fields (omit empty sides). Omit the row when `mcp` is empty and you did not call MCP this turn. Self-report MCP used via `CallMcpTool` or `FetchMcpResource` when the ledger is unavailable or stale; use source `CallMcpTool`. For resource fetches, format as `server ‚Äî resource:<uri>`.
- **Hooks (executed)**: Prefer `hooks_executed` from the ledger. List **every** entry verbatim (`hookEvent:script.ps1` or `.sh`). These are hooks that actually ran this generation ‚Äî not the full manifest. Do not list `hooks_configured` in the agent-facing table (that field is the static wiring snapshot). If `hooks_executed` is missing or empty but the ledger exists, fall back to `tracking_events` only when entries use the `event:script` format. If the ledger is unavailable, write `Hooks (executed) | (unknown) | not observable to agent`.
- **Source column**: `ledger` when taken from `active.json`; `context` / `Read on SKILL.md` / `Task tool` when self-reported.

## Enumeration (mandatory)

- **Never truncate** lists with `...`, `etc.`, `and N more`, or similar shorthand.
- One table row per Kind; put all items for that Kind on the row, comma-separated.
- If a Kind has many items (e.g. hooks), still list **all** of them ‚Äî wrap to multiple lines inside the cell if needed, but do not omit any entry.

## Constraints

- Do not repeat the user prompt in this section.
- In very short replies (one sentence), a minimal table is still required.
- Do not include model or token usage rows ‚Äî Cursor hooks do not expose reliable per-turn model slugs or billing tokens to the agent.
